# Agent Default Standards

- Read `AGENTS.md` at the start of every task.
- Use this repository's local standards as defaults, not generic framework defaults.
- Load only the `.agents/skills/*` files relevant to the current task.
- For data/fetch/metadata/API tasks, always read:
  - `.agents/skills/fetch-pattern/SKILL.md`
- Keep changes minimal, type-safe, and aligned with Next.js 16 App Router.
- Do not leave placeholder metadata/config values (for example `example.com`) in production-oriented code.
- Avoid brittle build-time demo fetches without fallback behavior.
- Run quality checks after substantive changes: `npm run lint`, `npm run typecheck`, `npm run build`.
